<h1>ANSWERS</h1>
			<div id = "post-ans" class = "post">
				<p>I don't think that a <em>Markdown</em> help page is an appropriate place for teaching users about HTML tags, however obscure they may be.</p>

<p>I see three options:</p>

<ul>
<li>Don't provide a Markdown help page. Provide an <em>editing</em> help page that covers both Markdown and HTML.</li>
<li>Provide a discoverable <a href="https://apple.meta.stackexchange.com/questions/390/editor-button-or-shortcut-for-kbd-tag">editor button</a> for inserting the <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code> tag.</li>
<li>Polish and link more prominently to an <a href="https://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/1777/what-html-tags-are-allowed-on-stack-exchange-sites">HTML help page</a>.</li>
</ul>

